			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you can get him to agree to fight you indoors then go for it, but I highly doubt he will go along with that.
<br />

<br />
Pummice can be found at most potion vendors (second door on your left from nexus stone in PoK) and right clicks 3 charges of cancel magic with a 3 second cast time. The reason you want pummice (at your level) versus a bard is that you will need to dispell maybe 30-40 times during the fight. 30 dispells will run you about 100pp, but better that than running OOM trying to dispell him.
<br />

<br />
I would stick with the air pet as the stuns could come in handy. Every time he gets stunned attempt a nuke. The bad news is that you don't have any of the fast acting nukes yet but you can still do alright.
<br />

<br />
He might get smart and attempt to mez your pet while meleeing you with bellow to interupt casting (at your levels it actually works for this). If he mezzes your pet pummice it to strip mez.  I like to cast the worst damage shiled on the pet before burnout. That way when the dmg shield wears off there will be a hole at the top of the pet buff list for detremental effects and you can strip root/snare/mez etc without removing burnout. This assumes that your opponent isn't going to attempt meleeing your pet. If he does just nuke away and feel free to throw a damage shield on then.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
