			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Really really hard to dot your pet unless the bard wants to fight you in PC and you can get that 90 minute fungal rash on him. I am not aware of any way to dot a pet at lvl 41 that wouldn't destroy him in the process.
<br />

<br />
The real question is how much plat are you willing to burn on beating this bard? You could go all out and buy a tash orb for your pet, maybe even a slow stick. Once tashed you could probably land bio orb and it would be game over. Check the bazaar for some golem wands as they have a pretty potent dispell that can be right clicked.
<br />

<br />
Do the quest in the warrens for that 5 charge snare item. Stock up on root nets and maybe even buy some heal potions (very expensive however). There is no question that you can beat him, the only question is how much plat are you willing to spend to ensure that you do?
<br />

<br />
Just thought that I would add that I got coined by a mage for the first time ever on my bard tonight. Was in PoJ with 2 other players blocking the doorway so I couldn't get out. The 62 fire pet was chain luring me through walls (apparently it doesn't have any LoS requirements). So if you have to fight a bard maybe try plane of justice in some of those tight hallways.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
